      "name": "BL - Brand Review",
      "settings": {
        "section_id": "brand-3",
        "bg_color": "#faf9f7",
        "number": "#3",
        "badge_text": "",
        "brand_name": "Meroda Cosmetics",
        "rating": "4.2",
        "price_text": "$36.00",
        "review_text": "<p>Meroda's color-changing foundation puts on a great show. The white-to-skin transformation is the most dramatic and visually impressive of any product on this list — if you're buying for the novelty factor, this is your pick. My teenage daughter was fascinated watching it shift color on my hand.</p><p>Unfortunately, the performance doesn't quite match the spectacle. The shade it settled on was in the right ballpark but slightly ashy, which needed correcting with a light dusting of powder. The formula itself is thinner than I expected, which made it easy to apply but meant it didn't provide enough coverage to address age spots and uneven pigmentation — things I'd really want a foundation to handle at my age.</p><p>The bigger concern is oxidation. Around the four-hour mark, the foundation started to shift darker. By hour five, I was a noticeably different shade than when I'd started the morning. That's a problem for anyone who needs their foundation to hold steady through a workday.</p><p>At $36.00, it's the most affordable option I tested. But the shade-matching inconsistency and oxidation issue mean you're getting what you pay for.</p>",
        "verdict": "The color-changing effect is genuinely impressive to watch, but the actual shade-matching technology needs work. The oxidation issue makes it unreliable for all-day wear.",
        "image_asset": "lp-comparison-foundation-brand-3.jpg",
        "image_position": "right"
      }
    },
