      "settings": {
        "section_id": "brand-4",
        "bg_color": "#faf9f7",
        "number": "#4",
        "badge_text": "",
        "brand_name": "Forever Bloom",
        "rating": "4.3",
        "price_text": "$42.49",
        "review_text": "<p>Forever Bloom's Bio Mimic Foundation has a lot going for it on paper. The 4.3-star Amazon rating comes from over a thousand reviews, the SPF 50 protection is the highest of any foundation on this list, and the color-changing technology works reasonably well. The shade it found for me was close — not perfect, but close.</p><p>On first application, I was optimistic. The formula felt light, blended easily, and the coverage was natural without looking like I was wearing makeup. For the first two to three hours, this was genuinely competing for the top spot on my list.</p><p>Then things went sideways. The foundation started settling into the fine lines around my eyes and the creases around my mouth, creating that papery, textured look that ages you instead of helping. By afternoon, it had also oxidized to a noticeably warmer tone — not drastically, but enough that I could see the shift in bathroom lighting.</p><p>The SPF 50 is a real differentiator, and if sun protection is your top priority, this deserves consideration. But for all-day wear on mature skin, the line-settling is hard to overlook. At $42.49, it's a solid product with one significant flaw.</p>",
        "verdict": "A frustrating near-miss. Forever Bloom starts beautifully but doesn't hold up where it counts for mature skin. The SPF 50 is excellent — I just wish the staying power matched it.",
        "image_asset": "lp-comparison-foundation-brand-4.jpg",
        "image_position": "left"
      }
    },
